I find it strange that Java is one of the few languages that don't implement a method like this. Anyhow I'm still learning Java and I thought I would give writing my own a go. Of course being new, this is probably very inefficient and messy so I'm looking for all help and suggestions on making it smaller, more efficient and neater:

[code=java]
public static String titleCase(String name) {
    String[] words = name.split(" ");
    String result = "";
    for (String word : words) {
        for (int i = 0; i < word.length(); i++) {
            String next = word.substring(i, i + 1);
            if (i == 0) result += next.toUpperCase();
            else result += next.toLowerCase();
        }
        result += " ";
    }
    return result.substring(0, result.length() - 1);
}
[/code]
